//Skills// function similarly to [[Aptitudes|▽ Aptitude]], having a minimum rank of 0 and a maximum rank of 5. Unlike //Aptitudes//, they are considerably cheaper to advance, though much more specific in their utility. 

When initially making a character select one //Primary Skill//, two //Secondary Skills// and three //Tertiary Skills//. The //Primary Skill// begins at //Rank// 3, the //Secondary Skills// at //Rank// 2, the //Tertiary Skills// at //Rank// 1 and all other skills start at //Rank// 0. 

//Skills// are advanced by spending an amount of //Experience// equal to the rank to be gained. See the table for more details.

